From: Andy Shevchenko <andriy.shevchenko@linux.intel.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Apr 2020 16:01:35 +0300
Subject: tpm/tpm_ftpm_tee: Use UUID API for exporting the UUID
Patch-mainline: v5.8-rc1
Git-commit: 8c872863b4400d0c8e31a2ac16389fcaaede5e3c
References: jsc#SLE-15209

There is export_uuid() function which exports uuid_t to the u8 array.
Use it instead of open coding variant.

This allows to hide the uuid_t internals.

Signed-off-by: Andy Shevchenko <andriy.shevchenko@linux.intel.com>
Acked-by: Jarkko Sakkinen <jarkko.sakkinen@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jarkko Sakkinen <jarkko.sakkinen@linux.intel.com>
Acked-by: Lee, Chun-Yi <jlee@suse.com>
---
 drivers/char/tpm/tpm_ftpm_tee.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/char/tpm/tpm_ftpm_tee.c
+++ b/drivers/char/tpm/tpm_ftpm_tee.c
@@ -241,7 +241,7 @@ static int ftpm_tee_probe(struct platfor
 
 	/* Open a session with fTPM TA */
 	memset(&sess_arg, 0, sizeof(sess_arg));
-	memcpy(sess_arg.uuid, ftpm_ta_uuid.b, TEE_IOCTL_UUID_LEN);
+	export_uuid(sess_arg.uuid, &ftpm_ta_uuid);
 	sess_arg.clnt_login = TEE_IOCTL_LOGIN_PUBLIC;
 	sess_arg.num_params = 0;
 
